					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-11225769#post-4222408</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-11225769/scp-4155#post-4222408</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 18 Apr 2019 05:42:03 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>RockTeethMothEyes</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4022320</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Reading this tickled a very particular bit of my brain that made me shiver in delight. It's an absolutely bonkers set of things slapped together into a cohesive and engaging narrative. Bat-eating ice cream cats is one thing, but the domino effect incited by the Foundation is thoroughly entertaining. This was an easy upvote from the start.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-11225769#post-4222399</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-11225769/scp-4155#post-4222399</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 18 Apr 2019 05:25:39 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>aismallard</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4598089</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Overall it's good, but I feel like the execution was a little too direct. Firstly, the weird cat creatures are not sufficiently elaborated on, and sort of take a back seat to the mcdonalds guy.</p> <p>I feel like the article would've been better structured if it focused on the cat, and instead it had an update or incident that <em>implied</em> they were the origin of the fast food ice cream, rather than state it outright.</p> <p>No vote.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
